caption.p:
Effects of compounds 1–3 on the IR-induced invasion of A549 cells: (a) cell invasion was assessed using Matrigel-coated transwell plates in nonirradiated and γ-irradiated A549 cells treated with 2.5 and 5 μM compounds 1–3, respectively; (b) quantification of invasion. The percentage of invasion is represented as the number of cells per field compared with each nonirradiated A549 cell group. Data represent the mean ± SD ( n = 3);
∗
p < 0.05;
∗∗
p < 0.005 versus the control.
